Waterloo first appeared as a [[census designated place]] in the [[2010 U.S. census]], one of ten CDPS ([[Acampo, California|Acampo]], [[Collierville, California|Collierville]], [[Dogtown, San Joaquin County, California|Dogtown]], [[Mountain House, California|Mountain House]], [[Peters, California|Peters]], [[Terminous, California|Terminous]], [[Thornton, California|Thornton]], [[Victor, California|Victor]], Waterloo, and [[Woodbridge, California|Woodbridge]]) formed out of the deleted [[North Woodbridge, California|North Woodbridge CDP]] and [[South Woodbridge, California|South Woodbridge CDP]].<ref name=2010CensusCA/>

The [[2020 United States census]] reported that Waterloo had a population of 534. The population density was {{convert|98.3|PD/sqmi|PD/km2|sp=us|adj=off}}. The racial makeup of Waterloo was 335 (62.7%) [[White Americans|White]], 1 (0.2%) [[African Americans|African American]], 18 (3.4%) [[Native Americans in the United States|Native American]], 16 (3.0%) [[Asian Americans|Asian]], 2 (0.4%) [[Pacific Islander Americans|Pacific Islander]], 100 (18.7%) from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]], and 62 (11.6%) from two or more races. [[Hispanic and Latino Americans|Hispanic or Latino]] of any race were 193 persons (36.1%).<ref name=DP1>{{cite web |title=Waterloo CDP, California; DP1: Profile of General Population and Housing Characteristics - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDP2020.DP1?g=1600000US0683626 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 11, 2025}}</ref>

The whole population lived in households. There were 207 households, out of which 45 (21.7%) had children under the age of 18 living in them, 117 (56.5%) were married-couple households, 14 (6.8%) were [[cohabitation|cohabiting]] couple households, 39 (18.8%) had a female householder with no partner present, and 37 (17.9%) had a male householder with no partner present. 65 households (31.4%) were one person, and 38 (18.4%) were one person aged 65 or older. The average household size was 2.58.<ref name=DP1/> There were 131 [[family (U.S. Census)|families]] (63.3% of all households).<ref>{{cite web |title=Waterloo CDP, California; P16: Household Type - 2020 Census of Population and Housing |url=https://data.census.gov/table/DECENNIALDHC2020.P16?g=1600000US0683626 |website=US Census Bureau |access-date=June 11, 2025}}</ref>

The age distribution was 89 people (16.7%) under the age of 18, 71 people (13.3%) aged 18 to 24, 97 people (18.2%) aged 25 to 44, 153 people (28.7%) aged 45 to 64, and 124 people (23.2%) who were 65{{nbsp}}years of age or older. The median age was 47.0{{nbsp}}years. For every 100 females, there were 122.5 males.<ref name=DP1/>

There were 217 housing units at an average density of {{convert|39.9|/mi2|/km2|disp=preunit|units&nbsp;|units|}}, of which 207 (95.4%) were occupied. Of these, 132 (63.8%) were owner-occupied, and 75 (36.2%) were occupied by renters.<ref name=DP1/>

